<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <meta name="description" content="Comprehensive Refund Policy for Vidyari educational marketplace with 7-day guarantee.">
  <title>Refund Policy - Vidyari</title>
  <link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="./images/logo.svg">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/font-awesome/6.5.1/css/all.min.css">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700;800&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
  
  <style>
    :root {
      /* Strictly Monochrome Professional Palette */
      --bg-body: #ffffff;      /* Pure white background */
      --text-primary: #000000; /* Jet black for headings */
      --text-body: #1a1a1a;    /* Near black for high contrast reading */
      --text-muted: #555555;   /* Gray for metadata */
      --border-light: #e5e5e5; /* Light divider lines */
      --border-strong: #000000; /* Strong structural lines */
      --bg-box: #f9f9f9;       /* Very light gray for section boxes */
    }

    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

    body {
      font-family: 'Inter', system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 0;
      background-color: var(--bg-body);
      color: var(--text-body);
      line-height: 1.6;
      -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased;
      width: 100%;
    }

    /* --- Layout Container: Full Width --- */
    .container {
      width: 100%;
      max-width: 100%;
      margin: 0;
      padding: 40px 60px;
    }

    /* --- Typography --- */
    h1 {
      font-weight: 800;
      font-size: 3rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin: 0 0 15px 0;
      letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      line-height: 1.1;
      text-transform: uppercase;
    }

    h2 {
      font-weight: 700;
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-top: 60px;
      margin-bottom: 25px;
      padding-bottom: 10px;
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-strong);
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      display: flex;
      align-items: center;
      gap: 15px;
    }

    h2 i { font-size: 1.2rem; }

    h3 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-top: 30px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    }

    p {
      margin-bottom: 1.5em;
      max-width: 100%;
      font-size: 1rem;
    }

    /* --- Header --- */
    header {
      margin-bottom: 60px;
      padding-bottom: 40px;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    }

    .back-link {
      display: inline-block;
      font-size: 0.9rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      text-decoration: none;
      color: var(--text-primary);
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    }

    .back-link:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .meta-info {
      display: flex;
      gap: 30px;
      margin-top: 15px;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      color: var(--text-muted);
      font-family: 'Inter', monospace;
      border-left: 3px solid var(--border-strong);
      padding-left: 15px;
    }

    .meta-item { display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px; }

    /* --- Notice Box --- */
    .notice-box {
      width: 100%;
      margin: 30px 0;
      padding: 30px;
      background-color: var(--bg-box);
      border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
      display: flex;
      gap: 20px;
      align-items: flex-start;
    }

    .notice-icon { font-size: 24px; color: var(--text-primary); }
    .notice-content { font-weight: 500; font-size: 1rem; }

    /* --- Eligible/Ineligible Boxes --- */
    .criteria-box {
      padding: 30px;
      margin: 30px 0;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    }

    .criteria-box strong {
      display: block;
      font-size: 1.1rem;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-light);
      padding-bottom: 10px;
    }

    /* Eligible - Checkmark style bullets */
    .eligible {
      background-color: #fff;
      border-left: 6px solid #666; 
    }

    /* Ineligible - X style bullets */
    .ineligible {
      background-color: #fcfcfc;
      border-left: 6px solid #000;
      border: 1px solid #000;
    }

    /* --- Tables --- */
    .table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      margin: 30px 0;
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }

    .table th, .table td {
      border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
      padding: 15px;
      text-align: left;
    }

    .table th {
      background-color: var(--bg-box);
      color: var(--text-primary);
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      font-size: 0.85rem;
      letter-spacing: 0.05em;
      border-bottom: 2px solid var(--border-strong);
    }

    /* --- Lists --- */
    ul, ol { margin: 20px 0; padding-left: 25px; }
    li { margin-bottom: 10px; padding-left: 5px; }

    /* --- Contact Box --- */
    .contact-section {
      margin-top: 60px;
      padding: 40px;
      border: 1px solid var(--border-strong);
    }

    /* --- Footer --- */
    footer {
      margin-top: 100px;
      padding: 50px 0;
      border-top: 4px solid var(--border-strong);
      display: flex;
      justify-content: space-between;
      align-items: center;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
    }

    footer p { margin: 0; color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
    
    .footer-links { display: flex; gap: 30px; }
    
    footer a { color: var(--text-primary); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.9rem; }
    footer a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }
    
    a { color: var(--text-primary); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
    a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    /* --- Responsive --- */
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
      .container { padding: 30px 20px; }
      h1 { font-size: 2rem; }
      .meta-info { flex-direction: column; gap: 10px; }
      footer { flex-direction: column; gap: 20px; text-align: center; }
      .footer-links { flex-direction: column; gap: 15px; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <div class="container">
    <header>
      <a href="/" class="back-link">&larr; Back to Home</a>
      <h1>Refund Policy</h1>
      <div class="meta-info">
        <div class="meta-item">
          <i class="fas fa-calendar-alt"></i>
          <span>UPDATED: FEBRUARY 2026</span>
        </div>
        <div class="meta-item">
          <i class="fas fa-undo"></i>
          <span>7-DAY GUARANTEE</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="notice-box">
      <div class="notice-icon"><i class="fas fa-exclamation-circle"></i></div>
      <div class="notice-content">
        <strong>Important Notice</strong> This Refund Policy applies to purchases made on the Vidyari platform. Since Vidyari primarily deals in digital products (e-books, documents, courses), there are specific conditions for refunds. Please read this policy carefully before making a purchase.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Refund Eligibility & Conditions</h2>

      <h3>1.1 Eligible for Refund</h3>
      <div class="criteria-box eligible">
        <strong>Your purchase may be eligible for a refund if:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>Request is made <strong>within 7 days (168 hours)</strong> of purchase</li>
          <li>The digital product has <strong>NOT been downloaded</strong> to your device</li>
          <li>The product file is <strong>incomplete, corrupted, or damaged</strong></li>
          <li>The product content does <strong>NOT match the description</strong> provided at time of purchase</li>
          <li>You had a <strong>technical failure</strong> accessing the purchased content</li>
          <li>You are the <strong>legitimate account owner</strong> and can provide proof</li>
          <li>The file <strong>does not open</strong> on standard devices/applications</li>
          <li>You had a <strong>duplicate charge</strong> error on your payment method</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <h3>1.2 NOT Eligible for Refund</h3>
      <div class="criteria-box ineligible">
        <strong>Your purchase will NOT be eligible for refund if:</strong>
        <ul>
          <li>The file has been <strong>downloaded to your device</strong> (even if not fully viewed)</li>
          <li>The content has been <strong>printed or saved</strong> locally</li>
          <li>You have <strong>accessed the file</strong> in any way (downloads count as access)</li>
          <li>More than <strong>7 days</strong> have passed since purchase</li>
          <li>You changed your mind about the purchase (buyer's remorse)</li>
          <li>The purchase was made <strong>under false pretenses</strong> or fraudulently</li>
          <li>You do not like the quality or educational value of the content</li>
          <li>The content was not suitable for your needs</li>
          <li>You shared or redistributed the content to others</li>
          <li>Technical issues are due to your <strong>device, internet, or software</strong></li>
          <li>The refund request comes from a <strong>different account</strong> than the purchaser</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Refund Timeline & Processing</h2>

      <h3>Processing Timeframe</h3>
      <table class="table">
        <tr>
          <th>Step</th>
          <th>Timeline</th>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Submit Refund Request</td>
          <td>Within 7 days of purchase</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Request Review</td>
          <td>1-3 business days</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Approval/Denial</td>
          <td>1-2 business days</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Processing Refund to Payment Method</td>
          <td>5-7 business days for cards; 1-3 days for digital wallets</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Total Time to Account</td>
          <td>7-12 business days</td>
        </tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-exchange-alt"></i> How to Request a Refund</h2>

      <h3>2.1 Request Steps</h3>
      <ol>
        <li>Go to your <a href="/purchasehistory">Purchase History</a> page</li>
        <li>Locate the purchase you want to refund</li>
        <li>Click "Request Refund" button</li>
        <li>OR email <a href="mailto:support@vidyari.com">support@vidyari.com</a> with:
          <ul>
            <li>Subject: "Refund Request - [Order ID]"</li>
            <li>Order number and transaction ID</li>
            <li>Date of purchase</li>
            <li>Reason for refund (brief explanation)</li>
            <li>Proof of purchase (screenshot of order confirmation)</li>
            <li>Proof that file was NOT downloaded (screenshot of account)</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <h3>2.2 What to Include</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Screenshots of order confirmation email</li>
        <li>Your account email address</li>
        <li>Order ID (starts with #VID-)</li>
        <li>Clear explanation of the issue</li>
        <li>Proof of technical issues (screenshot of error messages)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-copy"></i> Duplicate Charge Refunds</h2>
      <p>If you notice you were charged <strong>multiple times</strong> for the same purchase:</p>
      <ol>
        <li>Contact us <strong>immediately</strong> at <a href="mailto:support@vidyari.com">support@vidyari.com</a></li>
        <li>Provide proof of duplicate charges (bank/payment statement screenshot)</li>
        <li>Include all transaction IDs involved</li>
        <li>We will investigate and issue refund within <strong>5-7 business days</strong> upon confirmation</li>
      </ol>
      <p>Duplicate charges are processed faster due to their clear technical nature.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-tools"></i> Technical Issue Refunds</h2>

      <h3>4.1 File Cannot Be Opened</h3>
      <p>If the digital file cannot be opened with standard applications, email support with the error message, screenshot, and device type.</p>

      <h3>4.2 File Is Corrupted</h3>
      <p>Try downloading again from your account. If still corrupted, contact support with filename and error. We will provide a replacement link or issue a refund.</p>

      <h3>4.3 Download Failure</h3>
      <p>Try different browsers or devices first. Download failures due to your internet, device, or browser settings are NOT grounds for refund.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-not-equal"></i> Content Mismatch Refunds</h2>
      <p>If the delivered content does <strong>NOT match</strong> the product description, document the difference and contact support within 7 days. Minor formatting differences do not qualify.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-hourglass-end"></i> Refund Method</h2>

      <h3>6.1 How You'll Receive Refund</h3>
      <p>Refunds are processed back to the <strong>original payment method used</strong>:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Credit/Debit Card:</strong> 5-7 business days (banking processing)</li>
        <li><strong>Digital Wallets (PayPal, GPay, PhonePe):</strong> 1-3 business days</li>
        <li><strong>Bank Transfer:</strong> 3-5 business days</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>6.2 Refund Does Not Appear</h3>
      <p>If refund doesn't appear after the stated timeframe, check your bank account thoroughly and contact your bank before contacting us.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-percent"></i> Partial & Store Credit Refunds</h2>

      <h3>7.1 Store Credit Option</h3>
      <p>Instead of cashback, you may choose to receive <strong>Store Credit</strong>:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Credit is 10% higher than refund amount (e.g., $100 refund = $110 credit)</li>
        <li>Can be used immediately on any purchase</li>
        <li>Valid for 1 year from issue date</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-gavel"></i> Appeal Process</h2>
      <p>If your refund request is denied, you can appeal by emailing <a href="mailto:refunds@vidyari.com">refunds@vidyari.com</a> with subject "Refund Appeal" within 5 days. The decision on appeal is final.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Rights Protection & Fraud Prevention</h2>
      <p>We monitor for refund fraud including multiple requests, requesting refunds after sharing content, or systematic abuse. Accounts engaged in refund fraud will be permanently suspended.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-credit-card"></i> Chargeback Policy</h2>
      <p><strong>IMPORTANT:</strong> Please contact us FIRST before filing a chargeback. If you file a chargeback after rejecting our resolution, your account may be suspended and you may be charged a fee.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="contact-section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-headset"></i> Contact Refund Support</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:refunds@vidyari.com">refunds@vidyari.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>General Support:</strong> <a href="mailto:support@vidyari.com">support@vidyari.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>Response Time:</strong> 24-48 hours on business days</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2><i class="fas fa-sync-alt"></i> Policy Updates</h2>
      <p>Vidyari reserves the right to update this refund policy at any time. All changes take effect 7 days after posting.</p>
    </div>

    <footer>
      <div>
        <p>&copy; 2025-2026 Vidyari. All rights reserved.</p>
      </div>
      
    </footer>

  </div>
</body>
</html>